// This is how you can use HIGHER ORDER FUNCTION. (and debug feat.)
We could write a fuction called calculator doing one task at a time. ex) multiply.
then you'd code:
function calculator(num1, num2) {return num1 * num2; }
then call calculator(2,3;).
This would be annoying because if I want to add, I'd have to code calculator functionto be addition now.

OR you can make each function for 4 types (like below) and use HIGHER FUNCTION FUNCTION by include a function as INPUT!

For ex) function calculator (num1, num2, operator){
  return operator(num1, num2);
}



CODE itself---------

function add(num1, num2) {
  return num1 + num2;
}

function subtract(num1, num2) {
  return num1 - num2;
}

function multiply(num1, num2) {
  return num1 * num2;
}

function divide(num1, num2) {
  return num1 / num2;
}

function calculator(num1, num2, operator) {
  return operator(num1, num2);
}

NOW below are usable: 

calculator (num1, num2, subtract);

calculator (num1, num2, divde);
